{
  "stem": "2004.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now here, people come from Holland, which are used to live in a-- in the normal conditions.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they go from sort of from heaven to hell, in one day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We went from-- from heaven to hell in three years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was very gradual.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now you get hardened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "With each camp, you get a little bit more hardened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you get slowly accustomed to the conditions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Therefore, for us it was much easier to survive than for somebody who was living a normal life, and here he comes to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, the chances of survival are zero, under these conditions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's like you jog all your life, and you can jog 10 miles without any big problems.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But if you never jogged in your life, you try it, and you're going to drop after the first one or two miles.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You will be-- you will never be able to make it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That is a very, very-- this is about as close a comparison as I can give you under the circumstances.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I grabbed my piece of apple or orange.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was either one or the other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my friend-- and we were both standing in line.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I made sure one thing, that before I come to that German that was doing the selecting to the right and to the left-- now what I observed is that the elderly, the one that were walking with their stooped shoulders and their head down, they were automatically put to the left.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were told to go to the left.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I also noticed some people who could hardly walk.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had injuries of some kind or another-- to the left.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
